Title: Every row's trigger has the identical aria-label 'Actions' with no file context

Finding:
btn.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Actions') is the same for every row. A screen-reader user navigating the table by name or hearing the button announced hears 'Actions, button' for every row and cannot tell which file/folder's actions it controls. Accessible names for repeated controls should include the item they act on.

Fix instructions (follow exactly; make targeted, minimal changes):
In src/app/dom-builders.ts makeRowMenu (which receives `entry: FileEntry`), make the trigger's accessible name unique per row by including the entry name. Change `btn.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Actions')` to `btn.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Actions for ' + entry.name)`. Do not change any other attribute or the visible '⋮' textContent.

